DIARRHEA, POST-EARTHQUAKE - NEPAL: (CENTRAL REGION)
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Tue 28 Apr 2015
Source: Ekantipur [edited]
http://www.ekantipur.com/2015/04/28/national/diarrhoea-patients-on-rise-in-quake-hit-khokana/404576.html


With a lack of safe drinking water after the [25 Apr 2015] earthquake, people in Khokana village, on the southern outskirts of the Kathmandu Valley, have begun suffering from diarrhea.

Although the villagers initially got treatment at local health posts, the number of sufferers has increased, so they were referred to a better hospital and to the health camps run by the Nepal Army, said a local social worker, Nepal Dangol.

Similarly, Shivaram Baniya from Adarshashaul Higher Secondary School said that more than 100 diarrhea patients have been provided treatment at health camps run by a joint team of the Nepal Army and the Bangladesh Army.

