[The Patan district is one of the 75 districts of Nepal divided into 5 different regions, Eastern, Central, Western, Midwestern and Far Western. It as well as Kathmandu are in the Central Region, which is adjacent to the Gorkha District of the Western Region, where the epicenter of the earthquake was. As shown in the "see alsos" from 2014, there was significant cholera activity in the Central Region especially. Given a sanitary infrastructure that would facilitate cholera transmission prior to the tragedy, the dramatic effects of the disaster on the availability of clean, safe water should produce a significant increase in diarrheal diseases, including cholera.

A map of the regions and districts of Nepal can be found at: http://ncthakur.itgo.com/map04.htm. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3330811,139.]
